# BrowserWing API Quick Skill

Service base URL:
- `http://127.0.0.1:18080`

Health check:
```bash
curl -s http://127.0.0.1:18080/health
```

Known working executor endpoints:
- `POST /api/v1/executor/navigate`
- `POST /api/v1/executor/evaluate`
- `POST /api/v1/executor/wait`
- `POST /api/v1/executor/screenshot`

Examples:
```bash
# Navigate
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18080/api/v1/executor/navigate \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"url":"https://x.com/home","wait_until":"networkidle","timeout":60}'

# Evaluate JS
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18080/api/v1/executor/evaluate \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"script":"() => document.title"}'

# Wait for load
curl -s -X POST http://127.0.0.1:18080/api/v1/executor/wait \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"load_state":"networkidle","timeout":60}'
```

Notes:
- Prefer BrowserWing API as single route when requested.
- If media upload endpoint is unavailable in this deployment, report explicitly instead of silently downgrading.
- Keep Chromium process count under control before launching heavy flows.
